news.title: Bombay HC imposes Rs 20 lakh cost on Kakade Construction's builder and its director
news.para: The Kakades must pay Rs 10 lakh to Vistra and Rs 10 lakh to the State Legal Services Authority, directed a division bench of Justices M S Sonak and Jitendra Jain in a Dec 14 judgment.

news.title: GIFT City invites bids from global companies to build 7.54 lakh sq ft commercial tower
news.para: Bidders can be a domestic or international company, a consortium or a joint venture. As a co-developer of the project, the selected bidder will be required to design, finance, develop, construct, operate and maintain the commercial tower.

news.title: Bengaluru: Homebuyers approach KHRC as revenue department fails to enforce RERA penalty
news.para: With the revenue department allegedly remaining apathetic towards collecting the penalty imposed on a builder by Real Estate Regulatory Authority (RERA), hapless homebuyers have approached Karnataka State Human Rights Commission (KSHC) seeking a solution to their woes.

news.title: Telangana RERA directs Aliens Developers to complete Tellapur project and compensate buyer
news.para: The authority also ordered the developers to pay interest at 10.95% per annum for the delay in possession from Dec 2017, excluding the Covid-19 waiver period, until the flat is handed over.

news.title: Rajkot: 19 home buyers cheated of Rs 2.4 crore as builders flee with money
news.para: A complaint was filed by one of the victims, Rama Gadhiya, a retired employee of the state-run Pashchim Gujarat Vij Company Ltd (PGVCL), against Manish Kariya and Sanjay Bhandari, who cheated her of Rs 35 lakh.

news.title: Telangana RERA imposes Rs 6.58 lakh penalty on builder over unregistered villas in Isnapur
news.para: TG RERA also directed the developer, Maha Homes, to form an association of allottees, hand over necessary project ‘Maha Homes-Muthyam' documents and instal fire extinguishing systems immediately.

news.title: Singapore's Wee Hur to sell its student housing portfolio to Greystar for $1 billion
news.para: Under the agreement, Wee Hur will retain an indirect stake in the portfolio via its Australian unit through a 13% equity interest in Greystar.

news.title: Gross leasing of office space set to rise 14% to record 85 million sq ft in 2024: Cushman & Wakefield
news.para: The gross leasing of office space stood at 74.6 million square feet in 2023 across eight cities -- Bengaluru, Hyderabad, Mumbai, Delhi-NCR, Chennai, Pune, Kolkata and Ahmedabad.

news.title: Asking prices for property in UK falls by 1.7% in December 2024: Rightmove
news.para: Rightmove's data is not seasonally adjusted and the drop in asking prices - which followed a 1.4% fall in November - was in line with the historic average decline for the end of the year, the company said.

news.title: Property investment in China falls 10.4% year-on-year in Jan-Nov 2024
news.para: Property sales by floor area in January-November fell 14.3% from a year earlier, versus a 15.8% drop in January-October.

news.title: Centre's air quality panel for Delhi-NCR invokes anti-pollution measures under GRAP III
news.para: Poor air quality, caused by unfavourable weather conditions, often persists from November to January.

news.title: Goa: Comunidades and officials told to remove illegal and unauthorised dwellings
news.para: The office of the collector, in a memorandum, asked the administrator of comunidades of the central zone, Panaji, north zone, Mapusa, and deputy collectors of Tiswadi, Bicholim, Bardez, Sattari, and Pernem to implement the judgement passed by the apex court.

news.title: Rajasthan government issues notification to form development authorities in Bharatpur, Bikaner
news.para: ​​According to a statement issued here, the state government is continuously taking important decisions for well-organised and planned development in the urban areas of the state with large population.

news.title: New home prices in China fall at slowest pace in 17 months in November 2024
news.para: New home prices were down 0.1% month-on-month after a 0.5% dip in October, the slowest pace since June last year, according to Reuters calculations based on National Bureau of Statistics data.

news.title: China's regulators pledged to boost efforts to stabilize housing and equity markets
news.para: The government will promote the recovery of the property market through measures such as increasing demand and controlling the supply of land for new development, China News Service reported, citing Dong Jianguo, a vice minister at the housing ministry.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body forms six-member panel to acquire Harnandipuram land
news.para: The township will be developed on 521 hectares. GDA needs to acquire 501 hectares of land. Of this, the development authority has 11 hectares in its bank and needs to acquire the remaining land from eight villages.

news.title: Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar civic body cracks down on property tax defaulters owing over 1 lakh dues
news.para: Since Dec 12,CSMC has sealed as many as 10 shops located in different parts of the city. Stating that the tax recovery process would be carried out in a more rigorous manner in days to come, the civic administration has appealed to the defaulters to clear their dues towards property tax.

news.title: Maharashtra: Proposal to modernise 100 property sub-registrar offices to get approval soon
news.para: The proposal was put forth after multiple complaints from citizens about cramped spaces and inadequate facilities at property registration offices.
